# Allowlist model: ignore EVERYTHING, then un-ignore only what the weft
# Dockerfiles (deploy/docker/*.Dockerfile) actually COPY. This keeps the build
# context to a few MB of source instead of the whole tree (target/ alone is many
# GB), and it stays correct when new heavy dirs appear (they are ignored by
# default, never dragged in).
#
# The Dockerfiles COPY: rust-toolchain.toml, Cargo.toml, Cargo.lock, crates/,
# catalog/, .weft-warmup/. deploy/ is kept so the Dockerfiles referenced with
# `-f` are inside the context too.
*

!rust-toolchain.toml
!Cargo.toml
!Cargo.lock
!crates/
!catalog/
!.weft-warmup/
!deploy/

# Even inside the allowlisted dirs, never ship build artifacts or VCS/dev junk.
**/target/
**/node_modules/
**/.svelte-kit/
**/pkg/
.git/
**/.env
**/*.db
**/*.db-journal
**/*.db-shm
**/*.db-wal
